      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) must be computed for the primary quantity of interest (hemolysis index) across at least three systematically refined meshes. GCI on the fine mesh must be below 5% for required level 2.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels (2.1M, 6.4M, 18.7M cells) were used to compute GCI for the normalized hemolysis index. Fine-mesh GCI was 1.8%, well below the 5% threshold. Richardson extrapolation confirms monotonic convergence. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
