      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The quantities of interest (normalized hemolysis index, relative hemolysis RH) must be directly linked to the clinical endpoint (blood damage) and the regulatory decision criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate). Required level 2 mandates documented traceability from QoI to the COU decision.",
      "rationale": "The normalized hemolysis index (NIH) and relative hemolysis index (RH) are directly traceable to the clinical endpoint of blood damage. The regulatory decision criterion RH < 1 is explicitly defined in the COU and maps to the simulated QoI. Traceability is documented."
